 of the Francis report </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">of</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> the Mid-Staffordshire NHS Trust public inquiry and the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">government’s response to this. </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">We</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> look forward to working with the HCPC </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">to incorporate </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">responsibility relating to candour</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> into existing </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">professional st</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">andards</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, and support the expectation that the strengthened responsibility is expressed and implemented consistently by all the regulators relating to the professions</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The CSP </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">strongly welcomes</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> the proposal from the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Government for a strengthened and more s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ystemati</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">c</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> relationship between professional bodies and regulators. The CSP </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">supports this being </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">applied to the HCPC</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, recognising the number and broad range of professional bodies with which it needs to have strengthened links</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The CSP would like to see HCP</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">C’s focus on protecting the public brought to the fore more through reflecting a patient-centred approach to its activity</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, such as </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">strengthened requirements for </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">user involvement in pre-registration</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> education design, delivery and review</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The CSP plays </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">a </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">key role in ensuring</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> high</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> professional standards</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> within the UK physiotherapy profession</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, setting out clear expectations of members</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">’ professionalism through our </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">CSP Code of Professional Values </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">and Behaviour and Quality Assurance Standards.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> We see these as c</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">omplementing the regulatory requirements as set by the HCPC. </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The CSP also provide</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> quality assurance and enhancement resources that the HCPC uses as curriculum guidance for pre-registration programmes in physiotherapy to inform implementation of its own s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">tandards of proficiency and of education and training. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Again, we see these as strongly supporting the HCPC’s own standards and its en</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">forcement</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> of these.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Responses that we have made to the 2012 Law Commission review of the regulation of the health care prof</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">essions and the Professional Standards Authorit